content: SG&A as a percentage of sales for the fourth quarter of 2022 decreased approximately 80 basis points to 20.2% from 21% in the fourth quarter of 2021 due to lower incentive compensation and cost management strategies, which were partially offset by deleverage of fixed costs and higher marketing expenses. Gross margin decreased by approximately 60 basis points to 35.6%, driven primarily by deleverage of occupancy expenses on the negative comp., SG&A as a percentage of sales for the year increased 160 basis points to 24.4% from 22.8% in 2021 due primarily to higher marketing expenses and deleverage of fixed costs on the negative comp.
